Condition Type ABNORMAL-EXIT

Class Precedence List:

  ABNORMAL-EXIT, THREAD-ERROR, ERROR, CONDITION, T

Description:

  An error of type ABNORMAL-EXIT is signaled when THREAD-JOIN is called on a
  thread that ended abnormally. The ABNORMAL-EXIT can be initialized with a
  condition that precipitated the abort with the initarg :CONDITION, and this
  condition can be read by the function ABNORMAL-EXIT-CONDITION.

See Also:

  ABNORMAL-EXIT-CONDITION
